Generic single-database configuration with an async focus.

This is a minimal Alembic setup for managing database migrations.

The `alembic.ini` file contains the main Alembic configuration.
The `env.py` file is the script that Alembic runs to handle migrations.

## Usage

### Create a new migration
```bash
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Description of changes"
```

### Apply migrations
```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Rollback migrations
```bash
alembic downgrade -1  # Rollback one version
alembic downgrade base  # Rollback all migrations
```

### View current migration status
```bash
alembic current
alembic history
```

## Important Notes

- This setup handles both `DefaultBase` (global database) and `BaseModel_Base` (tenant/shared database) models
- All models must be imported in `env.py` for autogenerate to work properly
- The database URL is read from `app.conf.config.settings.DATABASE_URL`
